            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "The reproducer is nicely minimal. For the generated C++, the safer comparison target may be `nullptr`/raw pointer state rather than constructing a temporary `unique_ptr` from `NULL`, since `unique_ptr` deliberately has multiple constructors that make this ambiguous on newer GCC. A regression should probably cover both `!= NULL` and truthiness checks on `unique_ptr` attributes in C++ mode, so the fix does not only handle the explicit comparison spelling.\n",
